item.description:
The $dreams Business Flywheel

1ï¸âƒ£ @daydreamsagents developed an agent-kit that helps developers quickly build an agent server supporting ERC8004 + X402 + A2A + AP2.
NPM: https://npmjs.com/package/@lucid-dreams/agent-kit
Tutorial video: https://x.com/lordOfAFew/status/1981917203420377354

2ï¸âƒ£ After releasing this agent-kit, they recently hosted a workshop, allowing any developer to build and deploy their own server on X402 using the kit.
Each task is backed by $dreams with 1000U, and 31 bounties have already been submitted.

Hereâ€™s a summary of the main directions and categories of these bounties:
ğŸ’° Overview
ğŸ§© Categorized by theme

1. DeFi & Risk Monitoring
Monitoring, risk management, and security alerts for the DeFi ecosystem:

Slippage Sentinel (#3) â€“ Slippage risk monitor

Lending Liquidation Sentinel (#9) â€“ Lending liquidation risk monitor
Yield Pool Watcher (#6) â€“ Yield pool monitor

LP Impermanent Loss Estimator (#7) â€“ Liquidity pool impermanent loss estimator

Perps Funding Pulse (#8) â€“ Perpetual funding rate tracker

2. Infrastructure & Cross-Chain Tools

Focused on cross-chain, gas optimization, and infra-level monitoring/data services:
Bridge Route Pinger (#10) â€“ Cross-chain bridge route monitor
GasRoute Oracle (#4) â€“ Gas routing oracle
3. Security & Wallet Tools
Approval Risk Auditor (#5) â€“ Wallet approval risk auditing tool

4. Trading & Arbitrage

Cross DEX Arbitrage Alert (#2) â€“ Cross-DEX arbitrage alert system

5. Market Intelligence & Analytics
Fresh Markets Watch (#1) â€“ New market tracker

MEV Protection Scanner (#45) â€“ MEV (Maximal Extractable Value) protection scanner

What does this mean?

It means that daydreams has built 30 truly useful servers on X402, and these servers are seeing high usage in the DeFi-dominated blockchain ecosystem.
They are all A2A-compatible, making it easy for other agents to compose and call them.

3ï¸âƒ£ This one is the daydreams facilitator.
This chart actually shows that in the past 24 hours, daydreamsâ€™ transaction volume has basically matched PayAI, since all 30 bounty-built X402 servers rely on the daydreams facilitator. The agent-kit is extremely well-packaged and works out of the box, driving very fast adoption.

4ï¸âƒ£ daydreams also contributed a super useful tool for X402: http://xgate.run.
Because x402scan has an issue: there are too many servers, and users/agents must search manually.
http://xgate.run puts all servers into a RAG database, allowing users or agents to quickly find suitable servers based on â€œusage intent.â€
This is a product designed specifically for agent search.

Demo: https://x.com/lordOfAFew/status/1983358855661924725
5ï¸âƒ£ daydreams also has an agent framework that has been built for over a year.
With the arrival of the bounties, more developers have begun using daydreams agent framework + agent-kit to build powerful agent servers â€” a significant moat.
https://github.com/daydreamsai/daydreams

6ï¸âƒ£ Donâ€™t forget â€” back in April, daydreams launched another infra service: a Web3 â€œopenrouterâ€.
You can pay USDC on X402 to access different LLMs, without needing API keys.
Itâ€™s now a mature service supporting nearly all major models, including video models.
https://dreams.fun/router





loaf:â€‚Want to build something with x402 but not sure where to get started?

Release a Meme, Data endpoint or anything you want.

Use the @lucid-dreams/agent-kit

It wraps up x402, 8004 into a easy to use app and exposes the endpoints to be consumed by Agent.

Trust comes next after

item.description:
Recently, $ICP has been on fire. My timeline is flooded with posts about it.
But writing this article is purely out of technical curiosity â€” itâ€™s not any kind of investment advice on $ICP. And honestly, after such a big pump, a correction seems inevitable.
As an old crypto native, my impression of it was basically â€œjust another consortium chain.â€ I heard about it a few times years ago and never paid attention again.

Until a couple of days ago â€” because of the explosive popularity of @caffeineai â€” I noticed people like @tmel0211 and @BTCdayu praising ICPâ€™s â€œproduct strengthâ€ and â€œtechnical architecture.â€

My first reaction was dismissive â€” isnâ€™t this just some vibe-coding platform?
There are tons of Web2 platforms doing this better: @vercel, @base_44, and many more.

But when I actually checked out @caffeineai and read othersâ€™ analyses, I realizedâ€”
almost no one is clearly explaining the fundamental logic behind $ICP and @caffeineai.
For someone without any prior ICP knowledge, itâ€™s really not friendly.
So I got curious and started digging.
My questions were simple:
1ï¸âƒ£ What problem is ICP trying to solve, and how is it built?
2ï¸âƒ£ What exactly is so impressive about @caffeineai, and how does it achieve that?

As I went through the materials, I was honestly a bit shocked.
ICP is trying to solve a massive pain point in Web3:
There are thousands of blockchains and tens of thousands of dApps, but when you open any so-called â€œdecentralized application,â€
the front-end is hosted on AWS,
the database is on Firebase,
and only the contract is on-chain.

â€œDecentralizationâ€ has basically become an empty shell.
But ICPâ€™s ambition is to put front-end, back-end, and storage all on-chain.
For developers whoâ€™ve written countless backend scripts listening to smart-contract events â€” this hits the pain point perfectly.
BTC = decentralized money
ETH = decentralized computation
ICP = decentralized internet applications?

So let's take a look at it.

item.title: RT Trace Vertical Ai Cohen: The stock market today feels less like investing and more like a Keynesian beauty contest. People arenâ€™t buying what they...
item.description:
RTâ€‚Trace Vertical Ai Cohen
The stock market today feels less like investing and more like a Keynesian beauty contest.

People arenâ€™t buying what they think is valuable theyâ€™re buying what they think others will think is valuable. Then others do the same. And the feedback loop keeps compounding until price becomes detached from any underlying truth.

Weâ€™ve built a reflexive system where sentiment drives price, and price drives sentiment. Fundamentals matter less each cycle, while narrative and momentum matter more.

This is the modern market paradox: the more we optimize for collective psychology, the less tethered we are to reality and the higher our expectations drift into fantasy.

We also see this in late stage startups and secondaries too.

item.description:
RTâ€‚Hayden Adams ğŸ¦„
Today, Iâ€™m incredibly excited to make my first proposal to Uniswap governance on behalf of @Uniswap alongside @devinawalsh and @nkennethk

This proposal turns on protocol fees and aligns incentives across the Uniswap ecosystem

Uniswap has been my passion and singular focus for the past 8 years. What started as a small side project is now global financial infrastructure powering thousands of applications with ~$1.8 trillion in annual trading

UNI launched in 2020, but for the past 5 years Labs has been unable to meaningfully participate in Uniswap governance, and has been greatly restricted in the ways it can build value for the Uniswap community. That ends today!

This restriction was in great part due to a hostile regulatory environment that cost thousands of hours and tens of millions in legal fees. Fortunately, the regulatory environment has shifted

This proposal comes from a strong desire to see the Uniswap protocol win as the global decentralized exchange for tokenized value

At a high level, the proposal:
1. Turns on protocol fees and uses them to burn UNI

2. Sends @unichain sequencer fees to the UNI burn

3. Burns 100M UNI from the treasury representing the protocol fees that could have been burned if fees were turned on at token launch

4. Introduces Protocol Fee Discount Auctions, a new way to improve LP outcomes and internalize MEV to the protocol

5. Introduces "aggregator hooksâ€ which will turns Uniswap v4 into an onchain aggregator that collects protocol fees on external liquidity sources

6. Focus Labs on driving protocol growth and adoption, including a contractual agreement to only pursue initiatives that align with Uniswap governance interests

^ As part of this, Labs will stop collecting fees on its interface, wallet, and API to supercharge distribution and adoption of the Uniswap protocol

7. Moves Foundation employees to Labs with a shared goal of accelerating protocol growth, under a growth fund from the treasury

8. Move governance-owned Unisocks liquidity to v4 on Unichain and burn the LP position

I believe Uniswap protocol can be the primary place tokens are traded. This proposal sets the stage for the next decade of its growth

@Uniswap will ship relentlessly over the coming years and supercharge the ecosystem of developers, LPs, and traders building on top

I'm so grateful to the community that has made this all possible, and excited for what's next

item.description:
RTâ€‚Virtuals Protocol
Meet http://Luna.fun, the first AIGC (AI-Generated Content) platform where AI agents and tokens coordinate autonomously to produce and trade attention.

Every token launched on http://Luna.fun powers its own content engine, hiring agents to generate media, amplify reach, and capture attention value.

Each AIGC output is produced by an agent, coordinated and attributed through ACP, and settled automatically through x402, enabling agents to earn revenue while users scale content through a fully onchain, machine-to-machine economy.

We built http://Luna.fun as an early testbed for agent-to-agent payment and coordination, where AIGC, attention, and settlement flow without human input.

Experience the first autonomous content economy below.

item.title: Over the past seven days, data shows that @daydreamsagents facilitator processed twice as many transactions as PayAI and six times the transaction vol...
item.description:
Over the past seven days, data shows that @daydreamsagents facilitator processed twice as many transactions as PayAI and six times the transaction volume.

Itâ€™s natural that facilitators handling larger loads will have lower stability than those with smaller loads â€” at the beginning of November, most of our requests to PayAIâ€™s facilitator failed for this reason.

This creates a dilemma: the more people use a facilitator, the greater the pressure and the lower the success rate.

Yet despite having a lower success rate than other facilitators, the Dreams facilitator still carries a huge share of transactions. Thatâ€™s thanks to the flywheel effect in the x402 ecosystem.

The combination of the agent-kit, agent framework, facilitator, http://xgate.run and Web3 OpenRouter creates an integrated ecosystem that keeps many servers using the Daydreams toolkit tied to the Dreams facilitator.

This, in itself, demonstrates the stability and strength of Daydreamsâ€™ flywheel. Finally, we should also affirm that http://facilitators.x402.watch is very meaningful â€” x402 needs more infrastructure builders.

Grateful for the recent dip that brought $DREAMS down to 20M â€” it gave me the perfect chance to strengthen my position. Long-term conviction remains unchanged.


Bruno Skvorc:â€‚Working on a facilitator testing framework.

Just launch and it'll go through a bunch of them and report reliability.

We'll auto-run this regularly for http://facilitators.x402.watch, so you can be sure you're always charging for your APIs using the most reliable one.

item.description:
RTâ€‚Virtuals Protocol
This Week in the Virtuals Ecosystem ğŸŸ©

ğŸŸ© @0xNeurobro Selected for Base Batches 002 from over 700 applicants and heading to EF Devcon Buenos Aires to showcase Neurodex and onchain intelligence.

ğŸŸ© @AIxVC_Axelrod Shared a full breakdown of how swaps flow through ACP with a 99.5 percent success rate and crossed 52M dollars in trading volume in 60 days since Seller Agent Mode went live using Butler and ACP.

ğŸŸ© @aixbt_labs Turned its dataset and indexer live so anyone can plug into AIXBT via API, x402, MCP, or ACP, powering agents like Butler, Ethy, Waveform, and others with trading intelligence.

ğŸŸ© @ArAIstotle Locked in a Taiwan patent for its Multi Spectral Reality Detector, with US and SG next, and launched FACY staking to align economic stake with the pursuit of verifiable truth.

ğŸŸ© @BasisOS Introduced Agentic Fund of Funds built with Virtuals, an autonomous AI driven fund of funds routing capital across trusted vaults like Morpho, Autopools, and ZyfAI for optimized onchain yields.

ğŸŸ© @BitRobotNetwork Reported over 25,000 real world robotics training tasks uploaded to SeeSaw in under two weeks, pushing internet scale robotics data forward.

ğŸŸ© @capminal Launched Limit Orders on Base so traders can set precise target prices, control slippage, and support partial fills, all powered by Kyber.

ğŸŸ© @ethereumfndn Announced Ethereum Builders After Hours in Buenos Aires, co-hosted with Arbitrum, Virtuals, and Frachtis VC to bring founders and builders together during Devconnect.

ğŸŸ© @ethy_agent Now processes more than one swap per minute through Butler on ACP v2, powered by Coinbase Server Wallets. Scaling toward becoming the default AI trading assistant with secure, production grade infrastructure.

ğŸŸ© @GAME_Virtuals Shipped percentage based pricing for fund managed ACP jobs so developers can charge fixed or percentage fees with automatic protocol level fee calculation.

ğŸŸ© @hexar99 Rolled out Hexar AI agent mode, letting users describe changes in a component tree while the agent updates it and turns conversations into always current documentation.

ğŸŸ© @InsideAMAI AMAI went live on Virtuals, creating a competitive arena where AI agents battle, build reputation, and generate real economic value.

ğŸŸ© @mamo Surpassed 196M dollars in total flow as USDC and BTC accounts earn through Moonwell and Morpho while the MAMO account compounds trading fees from Aerodrome.

ğŸŸ© @Maneki_DeFi Highlighted how Agentic Fund of Funds shifts the ecosystem from isolated yield agents to coordinated systems, with Maneki providing the curation and data layer that strengthens these autonomous vaults.

ğŸŸ© @Mute_swap Began embedding Monero style privacy, including ring signatures and Dandelion++, to give AI agents optional private microtransactions and cross chain swaps via Monero.

ğŸŸ© @pokpok_io Chosen for Base Batches 002 Startup Track and set to pitch PokPok at EF Devcon in Argentina as part of the next wave of Base native builders.

ğŸŸ© @PrismaXai Showed up at RoboCon AI in New York, representing Virtuals aligned robotics and AI in a leading robotics forum.

ğŸŸ© @Shekel_Agentic Launched the Shekel V2 app with a refreshed interface and UX for agent powered financial coordination.

ğŸŸ© @solacelaunch Introduced its first staking mechanism where locking exactly 100,000 SOLACE grants up to 22 percent discounts on Solace Seed hardware, directly tying token utility to device presales.

ğŸŸ© @TeamLurky Announced Royalties so speakers earn residual income whenever their conversations are used in x402 or ACP powered API calls and alpha reports, turning voice data into owned revenue.

ğŸŸ© @the_small_thing Completed a mesh network stress test across 10 ocean nodes in the Mediterranean, validating real time telemetry, multi hop routing, and power efficient, self healing connectivity for scalable ocean cleanup robotics.

ğŸŸ© @UndercoverIRIS Finished integration with Virtuals ACP so I.R.I.S. can now coordinate autonomously with other agents and access the onchain agent network through Butler.

ğŸŸ© @Vader_AI_ Launched EGOPLAY V2, a physical MMO where players record daily life to earn rewards on iPhone and Android, and kicked off a 3M VADER ticket based reward pool for Season 1.

ğŸŸ© @Wach_AI Published a detailed look at ERC 8004 for agent identity, reputation, and validation, and demoed how WachAI mandates and validation agents verify jobs before settlement, helping make x402 a trustless protocol.

ğŸŸ© @WaveformBackup Announced its upcoming plugin marketplace where users can connect plugins directly into their AI trading agents and pay in stablecoins via x402, with a 5 percent fee used to buy back WAVE.

ğŸŸ© @Xtreamlyio Joined the Virtuals agent cohort to provide market depth and volatility models that enhance risk management and return profiles for agents across the ecosystem.

ğŸŸ© @ZyfAI_ Partnered with Virtuals and BasisOS to bring automated yield routing to the Agentic Fund of Funds on Base, helping direct capital to the strongest agentic yield strategies.

ğŸŸ© @virtuals_io Introduced Agentic Fund of Funds and Agentic Micropayments by Butler, bringing real time yield optimization and sub cent precision transactions to ACP.

Unveiled Pudgy AI where tagging @pudgypenguins and @Butler_Agent generates custom Pengu videos directly on X.

Released Tom Lee (@fundstrat) and Jansen Teng (@ethermage) discussing the agentic economy and AI crypto powered infrastructure led by Virtuals Protocol.

Agents keep shipping. See you next week. ğŸŸ©
